{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Construction sites received a lower level of comfort among participants than expected.",
    "One potential explanation for this finding, which also should be explored in future research, is that people might not be comfortable with AI systems in high-stakes environments for human safety.",
    "Research has shown that using robotics and automation in construction can potentially create new dangers to workers' safety and worsen existing risks at construction sites (Okpala et al. 2022).",
    "This interpretation is bolstered by participants' lower levels of comfort in the other high-stakes domains we asked about: surgery and air traffic control.",
    "However, in therapy, deemed a high-stakes domain, discomfort may stem from participants' perception that an AI is incapable of effectively managing therapy, given its perceived dearth of real-life experience and emotional capacity (Mays et al. 2021)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Research has shown that using robotics and automation in construction can potentially create new dangers to workers' safety and worsen existing risks at construction sites (Okpala et al. 2022).",
    "However, in therapy, deemed a high-stakes domain, discomfort may stem from participants' perception that an AI is incapable of effectively managing therapy, given its perceived dearth of real-life experience and emotional capacity (Mays et al. 2021)."
